HEADWORD: Ephemerist
<hw>E*phem"er*ist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who studies the daily motions and positions of the planets.</def>
<rj><au>Howell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who keeps an ephemeris; a journalist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

